    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 7 assessed credibility factors meet or exceed the required gradation levels for MRL 2. The 6 not-assessed factors are acceptable at MRL 2 per ASME V&V 40-2018 Table 1. Validation comparison shows NIH predictions within ±15% of FDA benchmark data across all 5 operating points. RH < 1 criterion satisfied at worst-case operating condition. The informal screening sensitivity study confirmed low parametric sensitivity of NIH to viscosity and rotational speed variations within the CPB operating envelope. Credibility evidence is sufficient to support the intended use decision for this Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2.",
